 :root: [UNIX] n. 1. The {superuser} account that ignores permission bits,
user number 0 on a UNIX system. This account has the user name `root'. The
term {avatar} is also used. 2. The top node of the system directory structure
(home directory of the root user). 3. By extension, the privileged
system-maintenance login on any OS. see {root mode}, {go root}.